</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="menu-tools">
<title>The Tools Menu</title>
<para>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycap>Z</keycap>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Zoom</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Allows you to zoom on a point (left click) or area (click and drag); double-click to reset the zoom level to the initial state.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycap>L</keycap>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Draw Time Line</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Allows you to temporarily draw a vertical line where you left click.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycap>S</keycap>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Select Channels</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Allows you to select channels in order to act on them (move them to compensate for an offset, change the amplitude...)</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycap>V</keycap>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Measure</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Allows you to measure the time and the voltage between two points.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycap>T</keycap>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Select Time</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Allows you to refine the time frame used to display the data.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycap>E</keycap>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Select Events</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Allows you to select one event in order to move it or delete it.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycap>N</keycap>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Add Event</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Allows you to add a new event (select the type of event from the submenu).</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="menu-Channels">
<title>The Channels Menu</title>
<para>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>C</keycap></keycombo>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Channels</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Show Channels</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Shows the selected channels.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>H</keycap></keycombo>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Channels</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Hide Channels</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Hides the selected channels.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>G</keycap></keycombo>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Channels</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Move Channels to New Group</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Moves the selected channels to a newly created group (either an anatomical group or a spike group).</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycombo><keycap>Shift</keycap><keycap>DEL</keycap></keycombo>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Channels</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Remove Channels from Group</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Removes the selected channels from their current group and puts them in the <guilabel>Undefined Group</guilabel> (the <guilabel>"?"</guilabel> group). This does not actually remove the channels from the data file.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycombo><keycap>DEL</keycap></keycombo>
</shortcut>
<guimenu>Channels</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Discard Channels</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Removes the selected channels from their current group and puts them in the <guilabel>Discarded Group</guilabel> (simultaneously acts on the anatomical and spike groups). This does not actually remove the channels from the data file.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<guimenu>Channels</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Synchronize Groups</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Synchronizes the anatomical and spike groups. The existing spike groups are discarded and replaced with the anatomical groups.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<guimenu>Channels</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Color by Anatomical Groups</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Colors the channels using the anatomical group colors.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<guimenu>Channels</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Color by Spike Groups</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Colors the channels using the spike group colors.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="menu-clusters">
<title>The Units Menu</title>
<para>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<guimenu>Units</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Vertical Lines</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
<listitem><para>Draws spikes for selected clusters as long vertical lines.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<guimenu>Units</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Raster</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
